<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Horse Queue</title>
    <%- include('partials/head') %>
</head>
<body>
<%- include('partials/header-nav') %>
    <div id="page-container">
        <h2 class="text-center my-3">Queue</h2>
        <div class="text-center">There are 3 horses in your queue</div>
    <div align="center" class="container-sm rounded">
        <table border="1px" class="table table-striped table-dark">
            <thread>
                <tr>
                    <th scope="col">Horse</th>
                    <th scope="col">Location</th>
                    <th scope="col">Last Visit</th>
                    <th scope="col"> </th>
                </tr>
            </thread>
            <tbody>
                <tr>
                    <td>Buttercup</td>
                    <td><address>123 Main St,<br>Farmingtown, CA 99877</address></td>
                    <td>9/10/2019</td>
                    <td class="bg-danger"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Tequila Sunrise</td>
                    <td><address>1100 Sunset Ave,<br>Fair Oaks, CA 95728</address></td>
                    <td>10/10/2019</td>
                    <td class="bg-warning"></td>
                </tr>
                <tr>
                    <td>Juniper</td>
                    <td><address>915 Hubbard St,<br>Elk Grove, CA 97587</address></td>
                    <td>10/30/2019</td>
                </tr>
            </tbody>
        </table>
    </div>
        <p>We can utilize bootstrap's table row color options to indicate rows where a horse has been waiting in the
            queue for longer periods of time. There are "bg-warning" and "bg-danger" classes.
            <a href="https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.0/content/tables/#contextual-classes">
                https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.0/content/tables/#contextual-classes</a></p>
    </div>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>
</html>